oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Arzo Mooneyham birthday party guests
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Children at Arzo Mooneyham's 49th birthday party, posed sitting in front of an American flag.

(L to R) Charlie Low; Elizabeth Mooneyham; R. B. Mears; John. W. Faun; Floyd Mooneyham; Gertrude Manus. Second row: Bessie Mooneyham; Mayne Mooneyham; Eva Mears; Gladys Mae Mooneyham. Flag was from casket of Private Floyd E. Mooneyham (1893-1918). Arzo Mooneyham (1874-1934) was a lifelong resident of Cannon County. Jodie Mooneyhan from image # 5982 was his son.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
